Package entity

Class Transaction

java.lang.Object
entity.Transaction
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Transaction extends Object implements Serializable
Transaction class is an entity class that stores the data and information that a normal transaction would have. This class allows us to track what transactions have been made, allowing us to find out who bought what tickets and the information of the buyer such as his/her name, number and email etc.

    • Transaction

      public Transaction(double transactionAmount, String name, String mobileNumber, String email, LocalDateTime dateTime, int movieID, String cinemaCode, ArrayList<Integer> seatIDList)
      Creates a Transaction with the given attributes
      Parameters:
      transactionAmount - total amount that was paid by the movie goer during the transaction.
      name - Name of movie goer who booked the tickets
      mobileNumber - Mobile number of MovieGoer who made the Transaction
      email - Email of MovieGoer who made the Transaction
      dateTime - Date and Time of moviegoer
      movieID - movie ID of the movie that was booked
      cinemaCode - cinema code in which the movie and session is being held
      seatIDList - arraylist of integers representing the seat ID of of all the seats booked in the transaction
